text.tspan: Flat: Flat, or flatness, describes an object or a condition that is very smooth and easy.
Flat design concept: Flat design is a style that does not use any extra effects to create a realistic or three-dimensional effect.
The style is characterized by having no drop shadows, bevels or gradients, an overall minimalistic look, bright but muted colors, bold — often retro — typography and
simple user interface elements such as buttons or icons.
Lack of depth, no gradients or shadows or bevels or three-dimensional effects.
Using simple elements: rectangles, circles, triangles and other geometric shapes.
Slightly desaturated colors (eg in Flatuicolors suggested colors.)
Minimalism, the importance of white space, space between text and other elements.
